wind-turbine maker, and  China Guangdong Nuclear Power Group Co. (CGNPCZ) 
plan to develop 800 megawatts of wind farms around the world.  The companies are exploring sites in Brazil,  South Africa ,
China and India, and plan to complete the projects over the next
three years, according to an e-mailed statement from Suzlon.  Guangdong Nuclear unit, CGN Wind Energy Co., has installed
3,000 megawatts of wind capacity in China. It has no operating
wind farms overseas, according to its website. Suzlon has plants
in China and India and sells turbines to most major markets
including the U.S. and Europe, according to its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
